  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening food security, agriculture and livelihoods in Somaliland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We will work with farmers across four communities in Somaliland to protect their land against extreme weather, making it suitable to cultivate a sustainable source of food to feed their families and earn an income, directly benefitting 1,620 people. In order to strengthen resilience, 230 small-scale farmers will gain improved access to water sources, including shallow wells and water pumps, and 40 farmers will be trained in local coping mechanisms. This project will also work in collaboration with the government to strengthen long term support for local farmers.</narrative>
  </description>
